Looking for a quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our
Harissa and Apricot Beef in just 20-25 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

== Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat.
Add the @Jasmine Rice{150%grams} and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{}
and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Beef ==

Meanwhile, heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @British Beef Mince{240%grams} and fry until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, cut the @Dried Apricots{40%grams} into small pieces.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Drain and rinse the @Chickpeas{1/2%carton} in a sieve.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic, @Chermoula Spice Mix{1%sachet} and @Tomato Puree{30%grams} to
the beef. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Lower the heat to medium, then stir in the apricots, chickpeas,
@Harissa Paste{50%grams}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%grams}, @Honey{15%grams},
@Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{150%milliliters}.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Taste the beef and season with salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of
water if it's a little thick.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}.

== To Serve ==

Share the rice between your bowls.

Top with the harissa beef. Enjoy!